Craftsman

Built by Hand

I am a hobbyist woodworker enjoying the process of constant improvement of my skills. I will make anything that captures my interest and have enjoyed building kayaks as well as furniture.

It is this type of project that I can then use in daily life that I most enjoy.

Method

The Making of a Piece

From the first conversation to the final finish—a process built on integrity at every step.

I

Consultation

We begin with an unhurried conversation about how you live, what you value, and what role this piece will play in your home. This shapes everything that follows.

II

Design

Drawn by hand on paper, the design emerges through iteration. I select the lumber personally—often visiting the mill to choose boards for their particular grain and figure.

III

Making

The work happens slowly, with hand tools, in a quiet workshop. Joinery is cut to last centuries. Surfaces are refined until they invite touch. No detail is left to chance.

IV

Delivery

Every piece is delivered personally and installed by hand. I provide care instructions and remain available for the life of the piece. This is the beginning of our relationship, not the end.

Commissions

Begin a Conversation

Tell me about the piece you're imagining. I take on a limited number of commissions each year and would be honored to discuss yours.
